title: Football: Bethlehem Catholic tramples Dieruff
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Another episode of The Antwon Keenan Show aired in the end zone at Bethlehem Area School District Stadium on Saturday night. 
Keenan ran for 172 yards and five touchdowns as Bethlehem Catholic defeated Dieruff 40-0 in an Eastern Pennsylvania Conference South Division game. 
Randy Terry added 89 rushing yards and a TD for the Golden Hawks, and Julian Spigner was 9 of 12 for 121 yards through the air. 
Keenan had scoring runs of 64, 1, 3, 1, and 4 yards against the Huskies. 
Devante Robinson had Dieruff’s most productive night on offense, taking 28 carries for 93 yards.
